DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_1').description: Beliefs which are unfounded, unrealistic, and idiosyncratic
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_1').label: FIPAN_1

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_10').description: Lack of interpersonal empathy, openness in conversation and sense of closeness, interest, or involvement with the interviewer. This is evidenced by interpersonal distancing and reduced verbal and nonverbal communication.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_10').label: FIPAN_10

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_11').description: Diminished interest and initiative in social interactions due to passivity, apathy, energy, or avolition. This leads to reduced interpersonal involvements and neglect of activities of daily living.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_11').label: FIPAN_11

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_12').description: Impairment in the use of the abstract symbolic mode of thinking, as evidenced by difficulty in classification, forming generalizations, and proceeding beyond concrete or egocentric thinking in problem-solving tasks
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_12').label: FIPAN_12

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_13').definition: Lack of Spontaneity and Flow of Conversation
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_13').description: Reduction in the normal flow of communication associated with apathy, avolition, defensiveness, or cognitive deficit. This is manifested by diminished fluidity and productivity of the verbal-interactional process.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_13').label: FIPAN_13

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_14').description: Decreased fluidity, spontaneity, and flexibility of thinking, as evidenced in rigid, repetitious, or barren thought content.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_14').label: FIPAN_14

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_15').description: Physical complaints or beliefs about bodily illness or malfunctions. This may range from a vague sense of ill being to clear-cut delusions of catastrophic physical disease.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_15').label: FIPAN_15

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_16').description: Subjective experience of nervousness, worry, apprehension, or restlessness, ranging from excessive concern about the present or future to feelings of panic.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_16').label: FIPAN_16

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_17').description: Sense of remorse of self-blame for real or imagined misdeeds in the past.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_17').label: FIPAN_17

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_18').description: Overt physical manifestation of fear, anxiety, and agitation, such as stiffness, tremor, profuse sweating, and restlessness.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_18').label: FIPAN_18

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_19').description: Unnatural movements or posture as characterized by an awkward, stilted, disorganized, or bizarre appearance.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_19').label: FIPAN_19

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_2').description: Disorganized process of thinking characterized by disruption of goal-directed sequencing, e.g., circumstantiality, tangentiality, loose associations, non sequiturs, gross illogicality, or thought block.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_2').label: FIPAN_2

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_20').description: Feelings of sadness, discouragement, helplessness, and pessimism.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_20').label: FIPAN_20

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_21').description: Reduction in motor activity as reflected in slowing or lessening of movements and speech, diminished responsiveness to stimuli, and reduced body tone
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_21').label: FIPAN_21

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_23').description: Thinking characterized by strange, fantastic, or bizarre ideas, ranging from those which are remote or atypical to those which are distorted, illogical, and patently absurd
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_23').label: FIPAN_23

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_24').description: Lack of awareness of ones relationship to the milieu, including persons, place, and time, which may be due to confusion or withdrawal.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_24').label: FIPAN_24

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_25').description: Failure in focused alertness manifested by poor concentration, distractibility from internal and external stimuli, and difficulty in harnessing sustaining, or shifting focus to new stimuli.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_25').label: FIPAN_25

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_26').description: Impaired awareness or understanding of ones own psychiatric condition and life situation. This is evidenced by failure to recognize past or present psychiatric illness or symptoms, denial of need for psychiatric hospitalization or treatment, decisions characterized by poor anticipation of consequences, and unrealistic short-term and long-range planning.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_26').label: FIPAN_26

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_27').description: Disordered regulation and control of action on inner urges, resulting in sudden, unmodulated, arbitrary, or misdirected discharge of tension and emotions without concern about consequences.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_27').label: FIPAN_27

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_28').description: Absorption with internally generated thoughts and feelings and with autistic experiences to the detriment of reality orientation and adaptive behavior.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_28').label: FIPAN_28

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_29').description: .= Diminished social involvement associated with unwarranted fear, hostility, or distrust.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_29').label: FIPAN_29

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_4').description: Hyperactivity as reflected in accelerated motor behavior, heightened responsivity to stimuli, hypervigilance, or excessive mood lability.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_4').label: FIPAN_4

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_6').description: Unrealistic or exaggerated ideas of persecution as reflected in guardedness, a distrustful attitude, suspicious hypervigilance, or frank delusions that others mean one harm.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_6').label: FIPAN_6

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_7').description:
Verbal and nonverbal expressions of anger and resentment, including sarcasm, 
passive-aggressive behavior, verbal abuse, and assaultiveness
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_7').label: FIPAN_7

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_8').description: Diminished emotional responsiveness as characterized by a reduction in facial expression, modulation of feelings, and communicative gestures.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_8').label: FIPAN_8

DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_9').description: Lack of interest in, involvement with, and affective commitment to lifes events.
DD(source='PANSS', variable='FIPAN_9').label: FIPAN_9

DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_1').description: The patient is examined as he walks into the examining room, his gait, the swing of his arms, his general posture; all form the basis for an overall score for this item.  This is rated as follows:
DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_1').label: COSAS_1

categories.1: Normal, free fall with loud slap and rebound
categories.2: Fall slowed slightly with less audible contact and little rebound
categories.4: Marked slowing, no slap at all
categories.5: Arms fall as though against resistance; as though through glue

DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_2').description: The patient and the examiner both raise their arms to shoulder height and let them fall to their sides.  In a normal subject, a stout slap is heard as the arms hit the sides.  In the patient with extreme Parkinson's syndrome, the arms fall very slowly:
DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_2').label: COSAS_2

categories.4: Marked rigidity with difficulty in passive movement
categories.5: Extreme stiffness and rigidity with almost a frozen shoulder

DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_3').description: The subject's arms are bent at a right angle at the elbow and are taken one at a time by the examiner who grasps one hand and also clasps the other around the patient's elbow.  The subject's upper arm is pushed to and fro and the humerous is externally rotated.  The degree of resistance from normal to extreme rigidity is scored as follows:
DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_3').label: COSAS_3

categories.4: Marked rigidity with difficulty in passive movement
categories.5: Extreme stiffness and rigidity with almost a frozen elbow

DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_4').description: The elbow joints are separately bent at right angles and passively extended and flexed, with the subject's biceps observed and simultaneously palpated.  The resistance to this procedure is rated.  (The presence of cogwheel rigidity is noted separately.)
DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_4').label: COSAS_4

categories.4: Marked rigidity with difficulty in passive movement
categories.5: Extreme stiffness and rigidity with almost a frozen wrist

DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_5').definition: WRIST RIGIDITY or Fixation of position
DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_5').description: The wrist is held in one hand and the fingers held by the examiner's other hand, with the wrist moved to extension, flexion and ulner radial deviation:
DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_5').label: COSAS_5

categories.2: Slight resistance to movement although the time to rotate may be normal
categories.3: Resistance is apparent and the time of rotation is shortened
categories.4: Resistance is obvious and rotation is slowed
categories.5: Head appears stiff and rotation is difficult to carry out

DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_6').description: The patient sits or stands and is told that you are going to move his head from side to side, that it will not hurt and that he should try and relax.  (Questions about pain in the cervical area or difficulty in moving his head should be obtained to avoid causing any pain.)  Clasp the patient's head between the two hands with the fingers on the back of the neck.  Gently rotate the head in a circular motion 3 times and evaluate the muscular resistance to the movement.
DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_6').label: COSAS_6

DD(source='SAS', variable='COSAS_7').description: Subject is told to open eyes wide and not to blink.  The glabella region is tapped at a steady, rapid speed.  The number of times patient blinks in succession is noted:
